**An interactive AI-powered museum experience using real artwork data from The Metropolitan Museum of Art (MET).**

This app connects Greek mythology with real historical artworks.  
You can browse mythic figures, view corresponding artworks, explore metadata, run big-data analysis, and generate AI curator explanationsâ€”directly inside Streamlit.

---

## âœ¨ Features

### ğŸ”¹ 1. Mythic Art Explorer (Main Feature)
Browse Greek deities, heroes, and mythic creatures.  
For each figure, the app automatically pulls **real artworks from the MET Open Access API**, including:

- Thumbnail grid (image-first)
- Paginated browsing
- Full modal detail viewer with:
  - High-resolution artwork image
  - Title, artist, date, medium, dimensions
  - Link to MET official webpage
  - **AI Curator Analysis (optional)**  
    - Overview  
    - Historical context  
    - Iconography  

---

### ğŸ”¹ 2. Art Data â€” Big Data Analysis
Perform dataset-level analysis on hundreds of MET artworks:

- Timeline (year distribution)
- Medium / material frequency
- Geographic / culture mapping
- Classification categories
- Tag / theme extraction
- Greek vs Roman identification
- Vase-painting recognition
- Accession-year trends
- CSV export

All analyses generated using **Plotly**.

---

### ğŸ”¹ 3. Mythic Lineages â€” Genealogy Visualization
A **treemap visualization** of:

- Primordial gods
- Titans
- Olympians
- Heroes
- Creatures

Color-coded, hierarchical, interactive.

---

### ğŸ”¹ 4. Interactive Tests (Fun Module)
Two personality-based quizzes:

- **Which Greek deity are you?**
- **Mythological archetype test (Jungian-inspired)**

---

### ğŸ”¹ 5. High Stability & Optimized UX  
- Image-first layout  
- Modal artwork viewer  
- Unique keys to avoid Streamlit duplication errors  
- Caching for fast reload  
- Graceful fallback when MET data unavailable  

